        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 1:27PM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 127 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Truscott, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 30 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crowell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
